The N dynamics module has already been ported and committed (commit `9c9a694`). The only unstaged changes are to `.ralph_last_output.log`, `.ralph_state`, and `PORTING_LOG.md` — which are state/log files, not the port itself.

**Summary:** The port of `CNNDynamicsMod.F90` → `n_dynamics.jl` is complete and passing all tests. Here's what was ported:

| Fortran Subroutine | Julia Function | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `CNNDynamicsReadNML` | `n_dynamics_read_nml!` | Set N dynamics parameters |
| `CNNDeposition` | `n_deposition!` | Atmospheric N deposition to soil mineral N |
| `CNFreeLivingFixation` | `n_free_living_fixation!` | Free-living N fixation as f(ET) |
| `CNNFixation` | `n_fixation!` | Symbiotic/asymbiotic N fixation as f(NPP) |
| `CNNFert` | `n_fert!` | Crop N fertilizer (patch-to-column aggregation) |
| `CNSoyfix` | `n_soyfix!` | Soybean N fixation (EPICPHASE model) |

The `params_type` → `NDynamicsParams` struct is also ported. All 10,791 tests pass including the 13 N dynamics-specific tests.
